<subsection xml:id="subsec-The-net-of-a-cuboid">
        <title>The net of a cuboid</title>
        <p>
            In the previous section, you identified a cuboid. Discuss what to look for when identifying a cuboid.
        </p>

        <p>
            In this section, you will sketch nets of a cuboid.
        </p>

        <activity>
            <title></title>
            <statement>

                <p>
                    <m>\textbf{Work in pairs}</m>
                </p>

                <p>
                    <m>\textbf{What you need:}</m> model of a cubouid and a pair of scissors.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Examine a cuboid similar to the one shown below.
                            </p>

                            <image width="50%">
                                <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                                <latex-image label="cuboid1">
                                    \begin{tikzpicture}       
                                    % Define coordinates for cube
                                    \def\side{6} % Side length in cm
                                
                                    \coordinate (A) at (0,0,0);
                                    \coordinate (B) at (\side,0,0);
                                    \coordinate (C) at (\side,\side,0);
                                    \coordinate (D) at (0,\side,0);
                                    \coordinate (E) at (0,0,\side);
                                    \coordinate (F) at (\side,0,\side);
                                    \coordinate (G) at (\side,\side,\side);
                                    \coordinate (H) at (0,\side,\side);
                                
                                    % Draw the cube faces with transparency
                                    \fill[orange!50,opacity=0.5] (A) -- (B) -- (C) -- (D) -- cycle; % Bottom face
                                    \fill[orange!30,opacity=0.5] (E) -- (F) -- (G) -- (H) -- cycle; % Top face
                                    \fill[orange!40,opacity=0.5] (A) -- (B) -- (F) -- (E) -- cycle; % Front face
                                    \fill[orange!60,opacity=0.5] (B) -- (C) -- (G) -- (F) -- cycle; % Right face
                                    \fill[orange!70,opacity=0.5] (C) -- (D) -- (H) -- (G) -- cycle; % Back face
                                    \fill[orange!80,opacity=0.5] (D) -- (A) -- (E) -- (H) -- cycle; % Left face
                                
                                    % Draw edges
                                    \draw[thick] (A) -- (B) -- (C) -- (D) -- cycle;
                                    \draw[thick] (E) -- (F) -- (G) -- (H) -- cycle;
                                    \draw[thick] (A) -- (E);
                                    \draw[thick] (B) -- (F);
                                    \draw[thick] (C) -- (G);
                                    \draw[thick] (D) -- (H);                    \draw[thick] (0,2,0) -- (0,2,3);
                                    \end{tikzpicture}
                                </latex-image>
                                
                            </image>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Identify and observe its faces, edges, and vertices.
                             </p>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Cut along the edges of the cuboid to unfold it.
                            </p>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Lay the opened cuboid flat on a surface.
                            </p>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Draw the shape of the unfolded cuboid.
                            </p>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <p>
                                What do you notice about the shape?
                            </p>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Compare your drawing with those of other groups.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
 
            </statement>
        </activity>

        <p>
            <m>\textbf{Key Takeaway}</m>
        </p>

        <p>
           <ul>
            <li>
                <p>
                    A closed cuboid has <m>6</m> faces. Each face is a rectangle. A net of a closed cuboid is made up of <m>6</m> rectangles.
                </p>
            </li>

            <li>
                <p>
                    An open cuboid has <m>5</m> faces. Each face is a rectangle. A net of an open cuboid is made up of <m>5</m> rectangles.
                </p>
            </li>
           </ul>
        </p>

